&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul data-list-tree=&quot;true&quot; data-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in mechanical design within industrial robotic systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with serial robotic arm operations and design constraints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in systems engineering principles: requirements development, implementation, verification, system integration, qualification and release.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in robotic systems design including electrical and controls engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Solidworks and PDM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in structural FEA and CF

&lt;p&gt;ICON is looking for a Mechanical Engineer II to help in the development of ICON’s latest print systems on the Phoenix Team. This team is responsible for delivering the machine known as Phoenix to Serial Production. As a Mechanical Engineer at ICON, you will be in a hands-on development and technical design role impacting the creation and support of well-designed, maintainable mechanical systems. This is a full-time, onsite role is based at ICON’s Austin, TX office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create design solutions with excellent engineering and documentation processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and create prototypes using in-house and external fabrication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform engineering calculations to support design work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of systems through to handoff for product commercialization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive engineering excellence and the adherence to the scientific method.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile and analyze operational, test, and research data to establish technical specifications for designing or modifying products, processes, and materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform a wide range of tasks on a daily basis (e.g. Transition from office work to field work at a moment’s notice).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS or MS in Mechanical Engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of professional work experience as a Mechanical Engineer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated knowledge of component manufacturing processes (including machining, rapid prototyping, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience leading large system development projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency using parametric solid modeling and CAD software to design and document parts and assemblies.&lt;/li&gt;
